• Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. CAPE TOWN - MPs will debate President Cyril Ramaphosa’s maiden State of the Nation Address in Parliament on Monday.
	
	Ramaphosa made bold commitments in Friday's speech and put out a uniting call to all South Africans. He's hinted at toning down, what he calls, a bloated cabinet. IN QUOTES: Promises Ramaphosa made in his SONA speech It's not clear when Ramaphosa will announce changes to his ministerial team. The new president has also vowed to intensify the fight against corruption. Youth unemployment and inequality also featured prominently. eNCA